1. Login to Codepen
2. Create a new pen
3. Set Babel as interpreter and add the React package
  - Select the settings icon in the JS pane
  - Set Babel as the JavaScript pre-processor
  - In AddPackages install React
  - In Add External Scripts enter the following these two in individual lines
    - https://unpkg.com/react/umd/react.development.js
    - https://unpkg.com/react-dom/umd/react-dom.development.js
  -  Now you're ready to write code.
  - In the HTML pane create the root div
    <div id="root"></div>
  - In the JS pane enter your hello HelloWorld
        ReactDOM.render(
          <h1>Hello, World!</h1>, document.getElementById('root')
        );
  - Second option is to view the Hellow World Tick pen
    - This creates the default HelloWorld program with the HTML and JS pages.
    - The code shows a basic function and the basic rendering into the the ReactDOM
